   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <pb facs="#facs_1" n="1" xml:id="img_0001"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_1_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>Prof. <rs type="person" key="Tillich, Paul">Paul Tillich</rs>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>Course Announcements for 1957-58.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>Lectures in General Education
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>Tuesday, Thursday, (Saturday) 11-12 a.m.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>Semester I
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/><Religion wikiData="Q9174">Religion</Religion>, <Arts wikiData="Q2018526">the Arts</Arts> and <Science wikiData="Q7762580">the Sciences</Science>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>The relation of religion to the arts and sciences in
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_9" n="N008"/>general, with special reference to their contemporary
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_10" n="N009"/>situation.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_11" n="N010"/>Semester II
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_12" n="N011"/><Religion wikiData="Q9174">Religion</Religion> and <Society wikiData="Q48204">Society</Society>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_14" n="N012"/>The relation of religion to the social, legal, educational
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_16" n="N013"/>and political problems, including the present historical
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_17" n="N014"/>situation.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_18" n="N015"/>Note: Although much of this is the same material covered in the
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_19" n="N016"/><Religion wikiData="Q9174">Religion</Religion> and <Culture wikiData="Q11042">Culture</Culture> course offered in 1955-56 as Humanities 127,
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_20" n="N017"/>Professor Tillich plans to offer these as two completely independent
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_21" n="N018"/>half courses and suggests that probably two entirely different
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_22" n="N019"/>course numbers be used. If there is any question on this, please
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_23" n="N020"/>contact him.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_24" n="N021"/><rs type="person" key="Leonard, G.C.">G. C. Leonard</rs> (Mrs.)
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_25" n="N022"/>Secretary to <rs type="person" key="Tillich, Paul">Dr. Tillich</rs>
            </ab>
         </div>
      </body>
